Below a tiny few of the new configuration options explained;
(NB: Please refer to the configuration script for more of the available
options)

CLOSED_SYSTEM		By adding this tooltype to the node it disallows
			the [GUEST] keyword (or whatever the localized
			equivelent is) from being recognised thus 
			disabling the ability for new users to even begin
			to join. This makes the system "Member Referral" 
			Only in a quick way.

LOCAL_SYSOP		If you add this tooltype it will FORBID any
			attempt to login as the Sysop from [REMOTE]
			This is for sysops who are at home and *KNOW*
			that nobody should be trying to login as them
			Only LOCAL Logins for the sysop will be allowed
			when this icon is used. The callerslog will be
			notified of any attempts to REMOTE LOGIN as well
			as the user being auto-disconnected before they
			even get the chance to enter a password.

USERNAME_RETRIES=	This allows you to set the maximum number of
			[Username] chances a user who logs in gets before
			they get disconnected. Default 2. <Range 1-5>
			NB: The sysop account has an override to this
			function... The Sysop account has only ONE chance
			at the password before getting disconnected.

USERPASS_RETRIES=	This allows you to set the maximum number of
			[Password] atttempts a user who logs in gets before
			they get disconnected. Default 2 <Range 1-5>

SYSTEMPASS_RETRIES=	This allows you to set the maximum number of
			System Password atttempts a user who logs in gets 
			before they get disconnected. Default 3 <Range 1-5>

NUP_RETRIES=		This allows you to set the maximum number of
			Retries at the NEWUSER_PASSWORD before they get 
			auto-disconnected. Default 1 <Range 1-5>

PWFAIL_FEEDBACK		If this setting is added it will not attempt to
			execute the external "PWFAIL" door. Instead it will
			use an internal password fail door. This will ask
			the user if they want to notify the sysop if they
			have failed their password and let them leave mail
			then auto-disconnect the user. Once a user has
			failed their password their access level regardless
			of what it usually is, is dropped to 5 during the
			message sending phase. Remote logins as Sysop simply
			disconnect without asking to leave the sysop mail.


"G" 	 		Goodbye command now asks user if they really want
			to disconnect.

"G!" 			Instant Goodbye.No checking for partuploads/etc. 
			just an instant 'normal' logff.

"VS" or "V"		Now the view command will allow viewing of ANY 
			file, be it a textfile or binary. It strips all
			non-ansi characters and replaces them with full
			stops... Also now changed to PAGE FLIP text
			instead of scroll.. for faster viewing..

"WHO"			Revamped command,
