The Sysop`s node (Node 00) can now be setup as 'REMOTE_NODE_EMULATOR'.
This allows you to fully 'test' the bbs as if you where logging in from
remote. You login with a term program (you can use the built in term
program) Then you can upload/download, etc. exactally like connecting to 
the BBS from remote. This uses the 'nullmodem.device', however in an 
'intellegent' way.. it knows if your using the nullmodem device so you 
Don`t need to type the usual, ATD, RING, RING, CONNECT 19200, etc.. You 
simply type 'ATD'<return> just as you would if connecting to a normal bbs
and it does the rest...




