                         Help on File-Directories;

Filename	This item tells you the filename of the program, Notice the
brackets []...  Within these contains the filenumber that corresponds to
that file. If you wanted to download this file you could select it file by 
its Name or Number. eg;	'TRASHV20.DMS' or '1'

UL-Date		This item shows you the Date and Time at which the file was
uploaded onto the BBS. This helps you to determine how 'new' the file is.

Filesize	This item gives you the length of the file (rounded off to 
the nearest KByte.)

Xfer-Time	This tells you time [HH-MM-SS] it took the uploader to send 
the file and the CPS they obtained.

File_Diz	This tells you if the file already contains a valid
File_description

No DL`s		This tells you how many time the file has previously been
downloaded since it was uploaded to the BBS. This is updated every time
a file is transfered and so does not slow down the BBS or require any
offline processing. It also means its always upto date.

UL-Node		Tells you what node the user uploaded the file on.






