conversion tool to convert your Ami-Express v3.xx system over to Swift.
If your an 'icon' type person you can always use the easy to use supplied
GUI Editor. Hardened sysops can edit the configuration script by hand 
using an ascii text-editor. This should make the move efforless and you 
can then begin enjoying the benefits that Swift (we hope) will bring you.

We will release this software as SHAREWARE because we feel that sysops are
being  forced into paying for the development of new Hydra BIDIRECTIONAL 
transfer system for /X. The scene is a funny old place and a BBS running old
versions of the BBS software will be 'percieved' as being SLOW or LAME by 
its members for not using the 'latest' versions.. Therefore we feel it is 
simply not fair that REGISTERED Sysops should have to spend an extra $55.00
to upgrade to the new system that supports the new hydra protocol. I`m sure 
that both "Big Boss and Major Theft" did actually spent countless hours in
understanding the Hydra protocol (its quite a complex beast!) and 
incorporating this function into /X BBS. So why should sysops NOT pay then? 
Well let me explain something to the uninformed out there. The Hydra Protocol
allows bi-directional transfers along with chat facilities... The PC Users 
have been enjoying these features for quite some time now. BUT Let me 
explain;

             The "HYDRA" Protocol © is actually PUBLIC-DOMAIN!

The specifications and Example source-code already WORKING on the Amiga 
is in the public-domain. The protocol system was ported over to the Amiga
by the author of Term 3.4 so why pay $55.00 upgrade for 'allergy' PD
Hydra protocol support?

You may all be asking yourselves by now, "How much will Swift cost then?"
Well Swift-Professional is to compete with Ami-Express 4.00 in the market
place. We hope we have implemented and are implementing features which
appeal to you as a sysop and user alike (sorry about the added security 
measures hackers!) As we are scene members ourselves ( I have been for
over 8 years now, back in the old days of BAMIGA-SECTOR ONE, ORACLE, 
THE ACCUMULATORS, etc) we feel we owe the scene a contribution in some
way.. we hope this program will be it. So because of this and because
we feel the prices to update to Ami-Express are so ridiculously HIGH
our prices will be ridiculously LOW!

We will release this product under the Concept of "SHAREWARE". Please respect
our wishes and pay this $15.00 if and when you decided to use the program. 
The program will be supplied with >NO< copy-protection or limitations but if
you do register we will make sure you obtain copies of the updates as soon as
they are released and you will support future development of this project.. 

if we do not get much support we may shelve the whole project and let you 
pay LightSpeed Technology Prices!


